\title{Structured Decompositions Jl}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Use when users ask about StructuredDecompositions.jl, structured decompositions,}

\subtree{
\title{StructuredDecompositions.jl}
\p{You help with Julia tasks involving StructuredDecompositions.jl. Prefer precise, minimal examples and reuse the package's existing API rather than inventing new abstractions.}

\subtree{
\title{Quick start}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb using StructuredDecompositions\stopverb}}
\li{Build a decomposition from a graph: \code{\startverb d = StrDecomp(graph)\stopverb} (optional \code{\startverb alg\stopverb} and \code{\startverb snd\stopverb} keywords).}
\li{Build from a shape + diagram: \code{\startverb d = StrDecomp(shape, diagram, Decomposition)\stopverb} or \code{\startverb CoDecomposition\stopverb}.}
\li{Inspect: \code{\startverb bags(d)\stopverb}, \code{\startverb adhesions(d)\stopverb}, \code{\startverb adhesionSpans(d)\stopverb} (pass \code{\startverb true\stopverb} for indexed pairs).}
\li{\startverb Lift a functor: use the bold-D function (type `\mathbf{D}` then Tab in Julia) with signature `D(f, d, t::DecompType = d.decomp_type)`.\stopverb}
\li{Decide a sheaf-encoded problem: \code{\startverb ok, witness = decide_sheaf_tree_shape(f, d)\stopverb}.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Guidelines}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb decide_sheaf_tree_shape\stopverb} assumes FinSet-valued sheaves; if you pass a \code{\startverb solution_space_decomp\stopverb}, ensure it is a \code{\startverb CoDecomposition\stopverb}.}
\li{\code{\startverb adhesion_filter\stopverb} (not exported) errors on \code{\startverb Decomposition\stopverb}; only use it with \code{\startverb CoDecomposition\stopverb}.}
\li{Use Catlab types (\code{\startverb Graph\stopverb}, \code{\startverb ACSetTransformation\stopverb}, \code{\startverb FinDomFunctor\stopverb}, \code{\startverb FinSet\stopverb}, \code{\startverb FinFunction\stopverb}) to build diagrams.}
\li{Prefer small, runnable snippets. If a full example is large, summarize and point to the references.}
\li{If a task needs ACSet schema definitions or Catlab graph basics, consult \code{\startverb references/acsets-bridge.md\stopverb} or load the \code{\startverb acsets-algebraic-databases\stopverb} skill.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{References}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb references/overview.md\stopverb} for the API map and key behaviors.}
\li{\code{\startverb references/examples.md\stopverb} for minimal usage sketches.}
\li{\code{\startverb references/graph-coloring.md\stopverb} for an ASCII-only end-to-end coloring example.}
\li{\code{\startverb references/acsets-bridge.md\stopverb} for ACSet/Catlab basics used by this package.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Scripts}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb scripts/quickstart.jl\stopverb} builds a simple decomposition and prints bags/adhesions.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example triggers}
\ul{
\li{"Make a structured decomposition for this graph."}
\li{"Lift a functor over a decomposition and decide a sheaf."}
\li{"How do I use decide_sheaf_tree_shape for graph coloring?"}
}
}
}